OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F406A1784229523
OL,3,CDartmoor ponies will be protected at
OL,4,Ccurrent levels, Government says
OL,6,FDartmoor pony populations will be
OL,7,Fprotected at their current levels,
OL,8,Fministers have said amid fears a
OL,9,Flivestock-counting method would put
OL,10,Ftheir future in danger.
OL,12,FCampaigners warned that requirements
OL,13,Fto cut grazing on the moor's commons
OL,14,Funder new contracts from the
OL,15,FGovernment's conservation agency
OL,16,FNatural England could lead to the
OL,17,Fremoval of up to 90% of hill ponies.
OL,19,FConservative leader Kemi Badenoch
OL,20,Flabelled the situation as "total
OL,21,Fmadness".
OL,26,@|D@[OU}D@HO]
