PN,40603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F406A1784229523
OL,3,CDartmoor ponies will be protected at
OL,4,Ccurrent levels, Government says
OL,6,FThe loss of ponies would be damaging
OL,7,Ffor the biodiversity of the landscape,
OL,8,Fas they are the best grazer of the
OL,9,F"monoculture" Molinia grass that has
OL,10,Fcome to dominate the moor, according
OL,11,Fto campaigners.
OL,13,FDartmoor hill ponies have been on the
OL,14,Flandscape for 4,500 years although
OL,15,Fnumbers have dwindled from 6,000 25
OL,16,Fyears ago to fewer than a thousand
OL,17,Ftoday, owing to historical policy
OL,18,Fchanges, and they have been declared
OL,19,Fan endangered breed.
OL,26,@qD@AOUqD@MO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
